{
  "stem": "1975.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And especially when the Russians have announced that they have made the Ribbentrop-- deal was made between Ribbentrop and Molotov, between Russia and the-- and the Nazi Germany, where they divided, partially, Germany took partially a part of Poland, and Lithuania as invaded, the three Baltic countries-- which is Lithuania, Latvia, and Estonia.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We actually start feeling that we are threatened, because suddenly, we saw what actually is happening to us and where-- the Russians who claimed that they are very prosperous, and they are very-- their country is-- that communism is-- is a great ideal.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We saw the way they came into Lithuania, and suddenly everything disappeared from the stores and from the factories, and Lithuania became a-- the economy has changed completely.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We have lost almost, I would say, right away the economic independence.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the market, the price, the prices starts going up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the fact is that we lost also our-- our-- the value for money, which was the [NON-ENGLISH], was the Lithuanian money.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was changed to the Russian currency.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it affected many merchants.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And especially in my father's business, and also most of the merchants who were dwelling in Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, you see, I was not at my-- at the city of [NON-ENGLISH], I was in Kovno studying in the Hebrew gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was 1941, June 1941.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was ready-- we had finished the gymnasium, and ready to start my studies in the university.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents wanted to send me to Italy to study medicine, because the medical school in Lithuania was very weak in a certain way, and it was very difficult, especially for Jews, to get in the university.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we start making arrangements.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
